kakasi
------------------------------------------
KAKASI is the language processing filter to convert Kanji characters to
Hiragana, Katakana or Romaji(1) and may be helpful to read Japanese documents.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.4.12-3
  cygwin-3.3.2-1
  libiconv2-1.16-2
  libkakasi-devel-2.3.6-1bl1
  libkakasi2-2.3.6-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.37-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  libiconv-devel-1.16-2
  libtool-2.4.6-8
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  http://kakasi.namazu.org/index.html.ja

Canonical download:
  http://kakasi.namazu.org/stable/kakasi-2.3.6.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack kakasi-2.3.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./kakasi-2.3.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/kakasi-2.3.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/kakasi-2.3.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libkakasi2-2.3.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libkakasi-devel-2.3.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(kakasi)
  /usr/bin/atoc_conv.exe
  /usr/bin/kakasi.exe
  /usr/bin/mkkanwa.exe
  /usr/bin/rdic_conv.exe
  /usr/bin/wx2_conv.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/kakasi.README
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/ONEWS
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/README
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/README-ja
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/THANKS
  /usr/share/doc/kakasi/TODO
  /usr/share/kakasi/itaijidict
  /usr/share/kakasi/kanwadict
  /usr/share/man/man1/kakasi.1.gz

(libkakasi2)
  /usr/bin/cygkakasi-2.dll

(libkakasi-devel)
  /usr/bin/kakasi-config
  /usr/include/libkakasi.h
  /usr/lib/libkakasi.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/kakasi.pc
  /usr/share/man/man1/kakasi-config.1.gz

